in martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnesen Buheler had at least 4 sons and 1 daughter with Paule Witmans."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1558–Male":"1558–Surnud","1559–Male":"1559–Surnud","1560–Female":"1560–Surnud","1565–Male":"1565–Surnud","1569–Male":"1569–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1 Jul 1565":"1. juuli 1565","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","14 Aug 1559":"14. august 1559","1565":"1565","28 Jan 1569":"28. jaanuar 1569","8 Nov 1558":"8. november 1558","19 Feb 1560":"19. veebruar 1560","1560":"1560","1559":"1559","Schiltach, Baden, Germany":"Schiltach, Kreis Wolfach, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1558–Male":"1558–Kuollut","1559–Male":"1559–Kuollut","1560–Female":"1560–Kuollut","1565–Male":"1565–Kuollut","1569–Male":"1569–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1 Jul 1565":"1. heinäkuuta 1565","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","14 Aug 1559":"14. elokuuta 1559","1565":"1565","28 Jan 1569":"28. tammikuuta 1569","8 Nov 1558":"8. marraskuuta 1558","19 Feb 1560":"19. helmikuuta 1560","1560":"1560","1559":"1559","Schiltach, Baden, Germany":"Schiltach, Kreis Wolfach, Baden-Württemberg, Saksa"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1558–Male":"1558–Décédé","1559–Male":"1559–Décédé","1560–Female":"1560–Décédée","1565–Male":"1565–Décédé","1569–Male":"1569–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1 Jul 1565":"1 juillet 1565","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","14 Aug 1559":"14 août 1559","1565":"1565","28 Jan 1569":"28 janvier 1569","8 N